Luke performed Inspection as part of Class Demonstration, however upon re-assembly realized that barrel clamp was not operating smoothly. Dis-assembled SYR module again on 13/04/20 and found that Chassis assembly was sitting on top of barrel clamp potentiometer (steel section), which was causing the barrel clamp to sit skewed slightly off-center, and barrel clamp was making contact with internal frame, causing improper operation. Installed Chassis first, followed by Barrel clamp, ensuring chassis was no longer sitting on top of barrel clamp potentiometer. Re-installed Internal Frame and ensured that Barrel Clamp was now operating smoothly. Successful re-installation. Photos and Video taken of Barrel Clamp smooth operation, uploaded to Dropbox. Hi Leanne and the RFDS Cairns team
Ive taken a look at the unit, and have not seen any obvious problems.

Possible causes:
1 . Latching alarms 
Zolls have latching alarms, meaning that an Asystole / VT / VF alarm will persist on the screen until it has been cleared by the user (by pressing the alarm silence button). If you are doing a dump test in the morning it may trigger an asystole alarm that will stay on the screen even if the dummy load has been removed and the ECG leads are hooked up to a perfectly healthy patient until the alarm is cleared.

2. Dry / Expired ECG Dots
The heat and humidity of Cairns may be interfering with the gel on the dots. If you can store the dots in their original packaging you may find they last longer and have less issues.We find this is one of the leading causes of problems with ECG readings for the QAS. 

If you do not believe either of these to be the cause, I am happy to get a quote for a new ECG lead and side panel where the ECG lead connects. The front panel also has some cracking where it meets the rear case and could be replaced to prevent any future fluid ingress if it gets worse (picture below). 

Please let me know if you have any more questions or want to proceed with a front/side panel replacement and new ECG leads and I will get back to you with a quote.
